out_desc_tool: This instrument was developed to measure the acquisition of the IS skills by the first grade children. The test consisted of 17 items. Examples of items found on the test are  color the picture of the largest triangle red, the middle size triangle green, and make an X on the picture of the smallest triangle. Reliability for this measure was found to be 0.88. Each of the items on this measure was read by the teacher while the students were com­ pleting them.

This test was prepared by a committee of over forty active high school chemistry teachers. The instrument consists of two parts of forty multiple-choice questions each, requiring eighty minutes for the total test. The content and construct validity of the examination are expected to be high since (1) it was designed by a large number of active chemistry teachers from all segments of the United States, and (2) the objectives of the course under study were the same as those of the examination.
